all the code is available publicly for you to review here - https://github.com/taoshidev/proprietary-trading-network and all of the rules implemented. All core logic is already finalized and ready for mainnet release. We're only waiting a week out for miners to prepare on testnet.

> Is second fee applied when reducing position (taking profit) according to point 4 of Rules. Is there any special reason of 10x higher fee for crypto?

Fees are only applied on the positional level, not on a per order basis (when you'd be taking profits). 
All fees are based on real exchange/broker fees that we see in the market. Forex / indices fees are generally lower and based on swap fees. Crypto fees are based on typical exchange fees and funding rates. I'd recommend reviewing the fees of each market against exchanges, what they typically are, and how they compare against our rates. You'll see strong alignment.

> There is a minimum registration fee of 5 TAO on the mainnet subnet.

Correct, floor fee to register will be 5 TAO. We suspect only the best trading strategies will enter due to the nature of the subnet, therefore we won't see continuous registration pressure. We expect the floor to be the price to enter at most times. Because of this, there needs to be a higher floor fee to join to disincentivize miners joining & taking aggressive trading strategies to try and gain an advantage. The goal is to get miners who produce trading strategies with steady gains, and proper R/R models.

> a) How often are the incentives granted to miners? Does it mean it's done once a 30 days (not like now where it is done once a 20 minutes or so)?

Incentives are granted every 30 minutes, very similar to TSPS based on a 30 day rolling lookback period (can be found in the source code). 

> b) How you define immunity, considering point 6 of Rules - does it mean the miner can apply super aggressive strategies, as the thresholds of 5% and 10% do not apply? What if miner drops to 0 during immunity - can it restart?

No you can be eliminated during the immunity period. Elimination is completely separate logic from deregistration. This can be due to exceeding drawdown limits, or being eliminated due to detected plagiarism.  Once a miner is eliminated from the network they will need to wait until they are deregistered if they are in immunity to try and rejoin.

> c) If I'm wrong, and the miners are incentivised regurarily as it is now  - how are incentives calculated for open positions? 

Only realized returns are considered for incentives, not unrealized.

> d) Another set of doubts relates to many markets available - do you assume miner should compete on many markets to gain as much total profit as possible, or rather specialize on 1-2 markets? (which basically also refers to the incentivication process - does it base on general profit across all trading pairs, or calculates separate rankings for each of the markets and assign market with incentives to be shared depending on particular market's popularity /calculated by miners trading on this market/) 

This is entirely dependent on your strategy. We look at overall return across all markets. Some miners will specialize in trading crypto, some forex, some indices. This is entirely on the miner. We are simply looking at return across markets on a per miner basis.

> First, because you don't really care about the current 'big' miners, who invested lot of time and money to optimize models with all the tools associated

This is building off the basis of TSPS. We'll continue to build and deliver for the community via open source models, data source partnerships, and core infrastructure as the basis for trading strategies. 

You've created great models, now its about who can create the best trading strategies using their models. Its a layer on top of your models with direct value for clients.  With this evolution, you can backtest your models & strategies before deploying to compete on PTN. The expectation is clear on the SN level, either the strategy is valuable or its not. This aligns with the way we see bittensor, hyper capitalistic. Either theres value or theres not on a return basis. Only the strongest strategies will receive incentive and power the greatest trading strategy in the world.

> Having one week time notice might be enough for the ones who do not significantly engage in current SN8, but for many it's just not enough - I leave this comment here hoping for your reconsideration on the timing assumptions.

The value for the network is much greater on PTN. Waiting delays value. That's not something we're willing to consider for the bittensor community, nor do we believe its in the ethos of bittensor. We didn't build on bittensor to ensure a few entities remain satisfied, we built to disrupt an industry and thats what we'll do.

We will shift the modeling techniques to be return based in our open source models & infra. That will be the way to approach the problem from a model perspective. Rather than concentrate on RMSE, concentrate on return to train.

Hey @kabar , great questions - I'll give you an update on our current design and objectives, although specifics might get tweaked as we tune parameters to get the incentive system right. We're currently looking at a distribution of 80% of the benefit to the top 20% of miners - the specific function used for distribution is here, which you can rebuild to model how we're distributing https://github.com/taoshidev/proprietary-trading-network/blob/f757137b9475df85920e6dbfc1d595bbf4515ce8/vali_objects/scoring/scoring.py#L48.

In response to your hypothetical situation with 256 miners, the top 50 would receive about 80% of the incentive, with the top miner receiving 3% of the overall incentive (compared with 0.13% for the person in the 100th slot). In a world with just 10 productive miners, the top spot might expect 55% of the overall weights. We will be regularly pruning out miners who aren't competitive or actively participating in the system, so 3% of the overall incentive for the top spot is the worst case scenario for the top miner.

To avoid the situation where a miner might get lucky with an early investment, we're introducing a historical weighting system for returns, where more recent return are more heavily weighted: https://github.com/taoshidev/proprietary-trading-network/commit/c8f1b7cc3959242e9e85e3c5276b7cbca2290385. Details on the weighting system can be found in this function: https://github.com/taoshidev/proprietary-trading-network/blob/main/vali_objects/scoring/historical_scoring.py . Under this weighting system, miners who are producing high quality returns at high frequencies will receive the highest rewards, distributed immediately after their positions close. The miner will continue to receive benefit from this positive return, but at an exponentially decaying rate  for the next 30 days.

*Some updates for implementation of out rollout!* 🚨 

**Plagiarism:** We want all of our miners to be confident they won’t get deregistered due to an accident with the plagiarism system. To avoid false positives which might accidentally deregister miners, we’re going to **manually oversee the plagiarism system** through launch and blocklist bad actors. We will be targeting miners who are explicitly copying the orders from other miners.

**Immunity:** Additionally, we will shorten the immunity period from **9 days to 5 days**. Given that registration happens roughly once per hour, a maximum of 120 miners will be in immunity instead of the current 216 for a 9 day period, which gives us a stronger guarantee that the top miner will not be deregistered.

**Weights: **Finally, we are going to adjust the weights distribution for the top miners. In the current weights distribution, 80% of the weights benefit go to the top 20% of the miners. We would like to heavily prioritize the top 10 miners, which would only comprise 5% of the miner population assuming 256 miners are registered. As such, we’ll be shifting to a **90% to the top 10% model**. Given that the historical return decay allows for more shuffling in the top spots, as it prioritizes returns from the past two days, there will be more opportunities to claim the throne.

As always, feel free to respond with questions and comments.

right - the goal of the subnet is to make a consistently competitive trading strategy. We track the returns for each miner over the past 30 days, and use this information to build a score for them. So if you have a a few great trades on the morning, you could be pushed to the top of the rankings that same day. We use a historical decay to discourage miners from sitting on a single good trade, that decay dampens prior positive returns but also dampens losses, giving miners a new chance to participate on bad returns. We then rank the miners based on their augmented historical return, and distribute emissions based on an exponential decay function, giving significant priority to the top miners. Details of both scoring functions can be found here: https://github.com/taoshidev/proprietary-trading-network/tree/main/vali_objects/scoring

The best way to get emissions is to have a consistently great trading strategy, which makes multiple transactions each week (the more the better). Here's a plot of an exmaple miner and their score / augmented historical decay score:
